~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ GREAT, AWFUL AND RARE COMPANY ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Well, what can i say about this game after my 1K hours of it:
SHOULD YOU TRY IT? - If you have friends, who can play for at least 2-4 hours, then yes. This game is outstandingly fun, beautiful and interesting for first 100-200 hours you may probably spent. 
SHOULD YOU PLAY IT FOR MORE THAN 200 HOURS? - PROBABLY NOT. Reason being the fact, that you'll slowly start seeing, that this game is actually awfully copying mechanics of it's own,and that it's same in everything and technically broken. And Dev's doesn't really seem to be caring\doing something about it.
Pros:
MUSIC - every time you hear it, you just fully get into song's atmosphere and overall mood. It's plain magnificent;
GRAPHICS - this game... is just godly-like with it's graphics;
STORY MODE (Pirate's Life Tall Tales) - comparing to usual TT's, they are awesome, they aren't as much time consuming as their old brother, they also have easier achievements and they ARE MUCH MORE interesting, as almost all of their missions are different, besides one theme of Davy Jones already can be a reason to try it out;
EMOTIONS - if you are playing with friends, than holy cow, you'll get alot of great emotions from your first hours.
Cons:
BUGS - i guess, i don't need to say here, you'll meet them, not as often as cheaters rn, but still;
HACKERS - a lot of them, and Rare doesn't seem to really care about it;
HIT-REG PROBLEM - "skill issue" - no, my friend, sadly, it's not. Many people including me encountered this abomination a lot of times, when you simply shoot a guy, and he just doesn't seem to get hurt at all. And sometimes this may lead to a fail for your side, even tho, you tried your best;
BORING, REPETITIVE CONTENT - what can i say, it says it's all really. Gold cosmetics ain't getting updated that much nowadays, even if they do - it's most-likely a simple recolour. Missions are just getting used to after 200 hours, as they all repetitive and have no difference, almost, at all, Athena's missions delay this feeling for a bit, but not for that much time. Bosses, doesn't matter if it's a boss from Story mode (original Tall Tales) or from Fort... or from Ashen winds... they all have one problem - they all are just reskin of one boss: they all have same abilities (ashen winds bosses have at least a bit of their of own, thanks for that, at least). Besides, game just seems to be awfully casual, like for a 6 y.o. kids, as killing bosses just as easy as taking a small candy from a child... who is giving to you. There is so much potential for fractions and events to develop into, but Rare just doesn't use it (same bosses, Hunter's Call being forgotten, athena doesn't feeling just as great as it is on your way to Pirate Legend title, Arena being forgotten and deleted in 2022);
COMMUNITY - you'll meet either really friendly and fantastic people, or you'll meet boring guys, or even worse, an absolute toxics. Thus the reason being, it's better to play with friends, or solo;
PIRATE EMPORIUM -  that's whole another topic: if you are giving your money to buy something great in a game about PIRATES, why do developers add stuff like fish-king? Or a plant-costume? Or an Undead, dangit, Gladiator? Why one of the best Pirate-Themed sets were added either a really long time ago, or with a Pirate's Life (Pirate's of the Caribbean) update? Does Dev's nowadays really don't have fantasy at all? Those sets are great, they look cool, but they don't belong in a game about PIRATES, for god's sake. There is still really brilliantly themed sets, which look aesthetically right, but i don't remember new sets being just as correct as some of the old ones;
GRIND - OOOOH YEA BABY, THIS GAME IS ALL ABOUT GRIND, THIS GAME IS BASICALLY BUILD OFF OF IT. And, unfortunately, it's one of the biggest reasons you WILL, for sure, get tired of it. 
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
CONCLUSION: 
At the end of the day, you should definitely try this game out, it's still really superb for some hours, but when you start feeling strange Deja Vu in it - get out, do not let it consume you like it did to me. (out of my 1000 hours only about 300 of them is what i really want to feel again). For the first 100 hours, you just see this colossal world, filled with joy, adventures and epicness. It's just like you opened a whole new universe. And it's really worth it, it will be great memories. Sadly, it will be left as a memories after some time, as you'll get tired of this game. I won't recommend it, it's just now that i saw all of the monstrosities of the game that i can't possibly recommend it... that is, if there wouldn't be one IF:
IF YOU WANNA SEE THIS GAME AS A LONG-TIME PROJECT - No, i do not recommend it, and i categorically against this game being viewed as such piece of product. 
ON THE OTHER HAND - if you wanna play a game for 100-200 hours, or even less - go ahead, it's worth it, but do not forget to take friends with you on this journey.

